§ 384.
-iþa
(OE. -þo, -þ, OHG. -ida, prim. Germanic -iþō with -i- from ja- and i-stems, Indg. -tā), used in forming fem. abstract nouns from adjectives, as
aggwiþa, anguish;
agliþa, tribulation;
dáubiþa, deafness;
diupiþa, depth;
dwaliþa, foolishness;
gáuriþa, sorrow;
